column10:
Good afternoon! As I was checking through preparing stations, station 2 was on preparing, trigger messages did not bring it to available. Upon checking GetConfig the FW was out of date with: 


 "key": "FirmwareVersion",
      "readonly": true,
      "value": "V1.00.79EVCS (BBOX: V1.32)"

I progressed to station 1 (parent) and pulled a get config (station was on same fw as above)

As I progressed through updating the firmware on station 1, the station had failed the download and pushed this code in OCPP:


FirmwareStatusNotification
Fri Jul 21 2023 17:57:14 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)
Request
{
  "status": "DownloadFailed"
}


- After "DownloadFailed" station pushed this log in OCPP:


FirmwareStatusNotification
Fri Jul 21 2023 18:02:13 GMT-0400 (Eastern Daylight Time)
Request
{
  "status": "Idle"
}
Response
{}

I have not attempted any station resets after the idle message as the station appears to be functioning. 

Assigning to software for insight. Thank you!

column10:
Michael Friedlander  drmf260@gmail.com  (646) 236-0013

 

 

1433 Palisade Ave ( loc_kIOEXF8zmW2zsCYgB8pOY )

 

He tried station 1 when he called in. He was trying to start the charge without him being plugged in so I asked him to plug in and then attempt. He got “error 303” popped up. I had him unplug and replug and try again but it was rejected. I thought maybe bc he had it unplugged when he was trying to start that it was overloaded so I had him move to station 3. It did the same thing with both his driver ID and the couresty one. Logs show it would go into preparing but then when we tried to start the charge it would reject. His account is all up to date and while we were at station 3 someone else went to station 1 and was able to start a charge with no issue.

 

He said this is his fourth time calling and each time the app doesn’t let him start a charge. He was irate so I was trying to just get him charging before attempting more troubleshooting bc he said he had done all of that in the past. He had a successful charging session at this same location and through the app on 10/8. Having you reset the station and then him using the card physically through the reader allowed the charge to start.

column9: 1433 Palisade | Station 2 | Connector Damaged
column10:
I received a call from this driver on 12/26 regarding the connector being stuck. I went through the normal troubleshooting of having the driver make sure the vehicle was unlocked then attempted a hard reset. A connector unlock command was also attempted but this did not work.

After a bit of troubleshooting, this driver said that the connector was broken. After clarifying which part was broken, they confirmed that it was the part that goes inside the vehicle's charge port. I asked if it was already broken when they inserted it and they did not know.

Eventually, the driver was able to unplug the connector

The driver agreed to send an image of the damage but has not done so.

column9: Day & Ross - S1 and S2 not charging all the way
column10:
Billy Rae reached out because stations 1 and 2 do not appear to be charging the trucks to 100%. 

The timeframe for which I was looking at the logs was over the past month, going back to November 30th.
 
Station 1:
There were only two status changes to a Preparing state, once on the 17th and another on the 28th. Neither appears to have started a session and returned to an available status right after.
 
Station 2:
On this station it looks like there were a few faults on it and of those, the ones around the times of charging sessions do appear to be related to communication issues between the station and the vehicle. One on the 20th was due to the vehicle closing the TCP communication.

I noticed the firmware on all of them are kind old so I put in 3 Tritium cases to get the firmware on all 3 up to the latest. Going to see if that helps with the issues on station 1 and 2. 

https://mytritium.com/charger/612300424/service/145598 S1 csb.23.1.5
https://mytritium.com/charger/612300419/service/145597 S2 csb.22.3.3
https://mytritium.com/charger/612300426/service/145596 S3 csb.22.3.3

There hasn't been many sessions on these stations because they have been avoiding using them. He did mention that: "We can test everything on the 6th so hopefully everything can we updated by then. If you check past logs there were so other issues occurring with Station 1 that was never resolved. Nicole was asking for some testing on the connector with a multi-meter but my staff locally can’t do this. I can schedule an electrician for a service call but would like to understand full scope and if multiple stations and items should be checked while on site. Please advise around this."
